<Author>wendybushellPerth
<Content>An Oasis in Legian! We stayed at the Padma for 11 days over Christmas and New Year. We had a garden chalet, in Block 19. Our room was upstairs and overlooked Jalan Padma. There was a lot of trees, shrubs and palms beside the perimeter wall which gave a high degree of privacy and acted as a noise buffer. The rooms were well appointed and very clean. The daily provision of toiletries (including a emery board) were a very nice touch.Breakfast was well catered, with different hot dishes to choose from on a daily basis. The staff were all very friendly and helpful, always smiling and happy to chat. The hotel was busy while we were there, but there always seemed to be room to move. This was our first visit to the Padma and we will definitely return! 
