<Author>niftyholidays
<Content>Great Holiday for your 50th Birthday We liked this Resort because of the Club Lounge area, when we arrived we were taken to this lounge for a drink and booked in to our room sitting down on a couch with a cocktail, what a way to start your holiday. The lounge is open from 5-7 for free and includes all drinks and cocktails Thank you SUMEI he was great everytime we walked in he knew what drink we wanted with out asking.We then were taken to our room slightly older than what we had hoped for but very comfortable once they finsh the renovations mid 2009 this will make a major difference. Because we had 2 people turning 50 in my friends room was his birthday cake what a surprise, this was a great way to finish the day.My wife is a Coeliac (no Gluten) so before we left I sent the Resort information and at breakfast they made her pancakes and anything else she would asked for they would go out of there way to make sure she would not get sick.If you are staying in the Club rooms then make sure you have breakfast in the private area they cook it for you and you can get other things the main area does not have we only had breakfast here twice and hwne we return we will always have breakfast here.All the Restaurants had been instructed on what was required if she did end up eating, the Japanese and Italian were fantastic. So make sure if you require special needs all you need to do is send an email before you travel and most Resorts will help as much as they can.The pool are is large but deep so if you can not swim stay in the shallow end but this end is still slightly deep. Most of the pool has a ledge around it so you can sit on this ledge and keep cool. You can also go over to the bar there is a shallow part so while you keep cool you can have a drink. The only problem I found around the pool bar there was not enough seats to sit while having a drink.The grounds are large so if you want a resort close to the pool this is not the resort for you, I liked walking through the trees and seeing the squirrels running up and down the trees was fantastic.I was dissapointed with the beach the sand is volcanic and dirty and dog crap so watch were you walk. But you must go for a walk the sunset's are fantastic and its great in the morning.We were asked if we wanted to go to UBUD for 2 days after we had been at Padma for 4 because the Resort had over booked at first we did not want to go until they showed us a picture. When we arrived we found ourselves in a beautiful forest with a Resort that only had 32 rooms, called KOMANEKA it had only been opened for 2 months, what a place we did not want to leave after 2 days. If you want a place to stay then I know you will love this place they have 3 Resorts and they are all fantastic 5 star++.Came back to Padma for the rest of our stay back to our same rooms so it was like going away for the weekend and then coming home. We were given 2 free dinners so we used them for my 50th in the Italian Restaurant all you can eat and we did, just before we finished they came out with my birthday cake singing happy birthday.I could go on talking about this Resort but I can only say if you want to go to a place that does not have many Children this is the place but make sure you book the Club room and get the special treats. The small amount it cost you will get back over and over again just by eating and drinking the 2 hours each day.If you like wine then drink as much as you can before you leave just like Phuket and other asian countries wine is expensive and watch the monkeys they will steal your glasses so hang on to them tight. I could go on for ever about this place so go and see for yourself but once again try and book the Club rooms we will be coming back to this Resort in April 2010. 
