<Author>podgirl2
<Content>Padma still a fabulous hotel This was the third time we have visited Bali (for July school hol's W.A) and the first time with our kids aged 16. 14 and 11. We have stayed all three times at the Padma. Our last visit was five years ago in 03, only six weeks after the Jakarta bombings.This time around I did some research into staying at other locations but can't get past the Padma in legian for it's convenience,proximity to the beach and being able to walk out of your hotel and shop (ie not have to jump into a taxi to find somewhere to eat or to buy a t-shirt) we particularly wanted all this as the older kids would be able to have a bit of independence if they wanted to. My travel agent tried to talk me out of staying at the Padma for the reason that it's expensive when you can stay cheaper in the area or go more upmarket and stay out at Sanur or Nusa Dua. I'm glad to I ignored her! Overall it's an exceptional hotel/resort and have enjoyed each three visits. It is looking better than ever. The gardens are absolutely magnificent. You would never have thought the hotel was full apart from at breakfast and around the pool. We booked two family rooms in the block which were ground floor, No availability for chalets (which we have stayed in previously). We were comfortable and rooms were clean and well serviced. Bathroom not as nice as in the chalets. The hairdryers (wall style) are complete crap and the shower surged between hot and hotter which was nuisance. I forgot to ask the older boys if theirs did in the room they had but they didn't mention it! You were supplied with 4 bottles of complimentary water continually. The last night we had noisy people above us (group of young guys) which woke us up and had we been staying longer I think this would have pissed me off! That could happen anywhere though.The pool area is good, very large but also busy. Yes people get up early and reserve their spot by the pool. if you are later than 8.00am you may not get one. Breakfasts are excellent and although the dining room seemed full after 8.00am ish there was never any shortage of food. The staff very attentive.As I said the location of the hotel is brilliant, right on the ocean (cross over the 'road' , although only foot traffic here) and very close to eateries and shopping. We ate along most restaurants in Jalan Padma and did not have a bad meal anywhere averaging about $40.00 AU for the 5 of us. Shopping here is as good as anywhere in Kuta without all the traffic. We weren't interested in the department stores so didn't go to Centro. The padma has markets which set up around the pool a couple of evenings of the week also which is handy if you don't feel like going out. While there i also went and checked out the Kamala Pantai in Legian as a few people had said it was good and much cheaper. I wasn't overly impressed. The room I was shown was clean but looked grubby (walls and furniture) and concrete balcony not that attractive. From my very quick impression staff seemed non-attentive (10 min's to get service at front desk when I walked in). and lobby was ugly. Pool area OK although gardens not a patch on the padma. I saw a visitor wheeling his own luggage to room and this would never happen at Padma where the staff will not let you do anything.Having thought long and hard about where to stay i am very glad we came back to the Padma and I wouldn't bother staying anywhere else if I went back. 
