<Content>Lovely Padma Lovely, clean hotel with lovely friendly staff, limited children's menu which is a problem especially if you're looking for healthy kids meals, children's pool is average but our 1 year old daughter still loved wading thru it. Breakfast at the Bella Rosa was fantastic and definitely a must for the Club members. It is a lot better than the cafe which is busy and just doesn't have that touch of elegance or service. Unfortunately, with having a 1 year old, we didn't make the most of the Club facilities - drinks and meals. What we did have there was nice and the free 1/2 hour internet service is a good touch. The meals at both the Bella Rosa and Tenkai were awesome and worth experiencing. I absolutely loved the Spaghetti Aglio Oglio. Meals at the hotel aren't cheap because of the service charge and tax. We used the kids club and babysitting service for our little girl. Because the Padma isn't really a 'kids' hotel like the Dynasty, there aren't a lot of kids at the kids club which can be lonely for your child if they are the only one there. Babysitters were lovely and were always on time. For our first time using foreign babysitters we were happy and will definitely use the service again. We would love to go back again. There is an abundance of laundry service, tailors - leather and general tailors in the area, which if this is what you're looking for, is a great thing to have outside your hotel door. The Padma in June is lovely and with the mild weather is a reasonable walk into Kuta - 30 minute brisk walk (not possible because of the footpath and the vendors stopping you along the way). 
