<Content>Loved the Padma I thought I'd add my review although three and a half years late!The Padma is a great place to stay in Bali, 10 minute walk along the beach to the heart of Kuta, the Legian market stalls and restaurants at the other entrance to the Padma. We stayed in a Garden Deluxe room which was very comfortable and we had access to the 'free' coffee, cool drinks biscuits during the day in the lovely club lounge area (with its own small pool area) and in the evening whilst sending emails to friends and family we indulged in as many cocktails, beers, finger food etc as we could fit in! The brekky was great and we had a choice of three different places to eat in. The pool is huge but very busy and I sat on the pavement a few times as the sun chairs were always taken  as usual alot of them only had lonely towels sitting on them awaiting for the shoppers to return!We ate at the Japanese rest and that was wonderful. We had a few evening meals of pizza around the pool pizza cafe which was fab at sunset. I would stay here again, but probably not with the 'cocktail extras' as we found we would stop what we were doing in Bali just to get back to the Padma to get our 'free-bees' and truth be known.. its all so very cheap anywhere in Bali so I wouldn't be tied down to the extra expenses of the 'club'  save a lot of money on the room package by just getting a deluxe room with out the extras.Hope this helps anyone thinking of staying at the Padma, I have stayed in Bali four times now  the Padma really is a lovely typical large Balinese Hotel.Enjoy :-) 
