<Content>Pleasant Experience My wife and I have just returned from a two week stay at the Padma Bali Hotel. We arrived on time and had no problems booking into our room however a small matter of an upgrade we requested had not been processed on thier register. This was quickly sorted out though. We got to our room, which was a garden deluxe chalet. Based on what I read on Trip Advisor, this was the room to be in. At first glance the room was spacious and looked neat and clean. As the days went by, we saw that the cleaning was definately not up to 5 star standard and definately not worthy of the hotels number one rating on this site. The shower looked as though it had not been cleaned for months as there was mould on the walls and the vanity was never wiped down. The bed was comftorble however we noticed on one particular day that the sheets were not changed. I accidently put a pen mark on the sheet and when the room was made up, noticed the same pen mark from the day before. Our room was on the ground floor. This was fine until people moved into the room above us. The noise was unbeleivable as chairs were being dragged across the floor all day and night and the feet stomping had to be heard to believed!. We asked to be moved but the hotel was full so we were stuck with the noise.On a more positive note, the hotel staff were very friendly and all staff greeted you everytime they walked past you. The pool was fantastic and never had a problem getting sun chairs. The bar staff are great and very friendly.We have been to Asia a number of times however this was our first trip to Bali and we were looking forward to the fun of bargaing with the locals. This was good for the first day, but it became very annoying after a while as they do not leave you alone at any time. We did the recommended dinner at Jimbaren at the beach to watch the sunset. This is a bit of a con as the sunset is just as good at Kuta and the cost of the meal was much more than you could have got elsewhere.Overall, I would reccommend the Padma and had a great holiday, but I would make sure we got a first floor room next time. 
